# 14. Como montar histórico de status por contrato

Agora um caso real.

Suponha a base:

```text
contrato | anomesdia | status
---------+-----------+--------
123      | 20260101  | OK
123      | 20260201  | ATRASO
123      | 20260301  | ACORDO
```

## Query

```sql
WITH base AS (
    SELECT
        contrato,
        cast(date_parse(cast(anomesdia AS varchar), '%Y%m%d') AS date) AS dt_ref,
        status
    FROM origem
)
SELECT
    contrato,
    array_agg(
        CAST(
            ROW(dt_ref, status)
            AS ROW(dt_ref DATE, status VARCHAR)
        )
        ORDER BY dt_ref
    ) AS hist_status
FROM base
GROUP BY contrato;
```

## Resultado conceitual

```text
123 | [(2026-01-01, OK), (2026-02-01, ATRASO), (2026-03-01, ACORDO)]
```

